desc: Determines if the type is a list type.

name: isMapType
desc: Determines if the type is a map type or a generic key-value container type.

name: isNonLoadableJetLeafFile
desc: Determines if a JetLeaf file should not be loaded.

name: isPartOf
desc: Checks if content contains a part of directive.

name: isSkippableJetLeafPackage
desc: Determines if a JetLeaf package should be skipped during scanning.

name: isStringAListType
desc: Determines if the type is a list type.

name: isStringAMapType
desc: Determines if the type string represents a map or key-value container type.

name: isTest
desc: Checks if content is a test file.

name: matchesAnyFile
desc: Matches a file path against a list of files.

name: matchesAnyPattern
desc: Matches input against a list of patterns.

name: resolveUri
desc: Resolves a package URI to its file system location.

name: shouldNotIncludeLibrary
desc: Determines if a library should be excluded based on loader configuration.

name: shouldNotIncludePath
desc: Determines if a path should be excluded based on loader configuration.

name: stripComments
desc: Strip comments from source code

name: SourceDeclaration
desc: A declaration that originates directly from source-level Dart code.

name: getAnnotations
desc: Returns all annotations applied to this declaration in source code.

name: getDebugIdentifier
desc: Returns the stable debug identifier for this entity.

name: getSourceLocation
desc:
Returns the URI pointing to the source location where this declaration
is defined.

name: toJson
desc: Serializes this declaration into a JSON-compatible map.

name: SourceLibrary
desc:
A first-class representation of a Dart library‚Äôs source code within
the JetLeaf framework. SourceLibrary is the canonical source-level library abstraction in
JetLeaf. It bridges file systems, packages, analyzers, and generators while
remaining lightweight, stable, and environment-agnostic.

name: getDebugIdentifier
desc: Returns a stable debug identifier for this library.

name: getName
desc: Returns the logical name of this source library.

name: getPackage
desc: Returns the Package that owns and contains this library.

name: getSourceLocation
desc:
Returns the physical or logical source location where this library
originates.

name: getUri
desc: Returns the canonical URI string of this library.

name: hashCode
desc: The hash code for this object.

name: isSdkLibrary
desc:
Indicates whether this library is part of the Dart SDK.
isSdkLibrary acts as a classification signal that allows JetLeaf to
distinguish between platform-provided libraries and user-controlled
source code, ensuring correct behavior across analysis, reflection,
and generation phases.

name: operator ==
desc: The equality operator.

name: sourceCode
desc: Returns the raw Dart source code of this library.

name: StdExtension
desc: Extension to simulate Java's System.out and System.err utilities in Dart.

name: print
desc: Prints a string without a newline (like System.out.print)

name: printErr
desc: Prints to stderr with a newline.

name: printf
desc:
Prints a formatted string using Dart's string interpolation.
Simulates Java-style printf.

name: println
desc: Prints a string followed by a newline (like System.out.println)

name: System
desc: Internal system facade for the JetLeaf framework.

name: SystemDetector
desc: Strategy interface for detecting and creating SystemEnvironment instances.

name: SystemDetector.new
desc: Strategy interface for detecting and creating SystemEnvironment instances.

name: canDetect
desc: Returns true if this detector can handle the current environment

name: detect
desc: Detects the current system environment and returns a configured instance

name: getPriority
desc: Returns the priority of this detector (higher values take precedence)

name: SystemExtension
desc:
Extension on InternalSystemContext that provides access to system-level
and environment-related properties similar to Java's System.getProperties()
and System.getenv().

name: getEnv
desc:
Extension on InternalSystemContext that provides access to system-level
and environment-related properties similar to Java's System.getProperties()
and System.getenv().

name: getEnvVar
desc: Returns the environment variable value for the given name, or null if not defined.

name: getProperties
desc:
Extension on InternalSystemContext that provides access to system-level
and environment-related properties similar to Java's System.getProperties()
and System.getenv().

name: getProperty
desc: Returns the system property value for the given name, or null if not found.

name: SystemProperties
desc:
The SystemProperties interface provides a clean, method-based API
for querying the runtime environment. Unlike direct property access,
all system state is exposed via methods to enforce immutability
and ensure consistent naming conventions.

name: getCompilationMode
desc: Returns the current Dart VM CompilationMode.

name: getConfigurationCount
desc: Returns the number of discovered configuration classes.

name: getDependencyCount
desc: Returns the number of resolved dependencies in the application context.

name: getEntrypoint
desc: Returns the application entry point file path.

name: getLaunchCommand
desc: Returns the full command used to launch the application.

name: isDevelopmentMode
desc: Returns true if the application is running in development mode.

name: isIdeRunning
desc: Returns true if the application was launched from an IDE environment.

name: isProductionMode
desc: Returns true if the application is running in production mode.

name: isRunningAot
desc: Returns true if the application is running with AOT (Ahead-of-Time) compilation.

name: isRunningFromDill
desc: Returns true if the application is running from a precompiled .dill file.

name: isRunningJit
desc: Returns true if the application is running with JIT (Just-in-Time) compilation.

name: isWatchModeEnabled
desc: Returns true if the application is running in watch / hot-reload mode.

name: Throwable
desc: Base class for all throwable exceptions in JetLeaf.

name: getCause
desc: The cause of this exception, if any.

name: getMessage
desc: The message associated with this exception.

name: getStackTrace
desc: The stack trace associated with this exception.

name: hashCode
desc: The hash code for this object.

name: operator ==
desc: The equality operator.

name: ToString
desc:
A mixin that provides customizable toString implementation using the same
properties defined in EqualsAndHashCode.equalizedProperties.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: ToStringOptions
desc: Configuration options for customizing toString output in JetLeaf objects.

name: COMPACT
desc: Compact format: parameter names excluded, single-line format.

name: COMPACT_MULTILINE
desc: Multi-line format: parameter names excluded.

name: MULTILINE
desc: Multi-line format: parameter names included, each on a new line.

name: SMART_NAMES
desc: Smart name generator that infers names from common property patterns:

name: STANDARD
desc: Default options: parameter names included, single-line format.

name: TYPE_BASED_NAMES
desc:
Type-based generator that uses the runtime type as parameter name.
Example: User(string: Alice, int: 42)

name: ToStringOptions.new
desc: Configuration options for customizing toString output in JetLeaf objects.

name: customParameterNameGenerator
desc: Custom generator for parameter names based on property values and indices.

name: customParameterNames
desc:
Explicit parameter names (overrides inference).
Must match the length of EqualsAndHashCode.equalizedProperties.

name: customSeparator
desc:
Custom separator between parameters.
Defaults to ", " or ",\n" depending on useNewlines.

name: includeClassName
desc: Whether to include the class name in output.

name: includeParameterNames
desc: Whether to include parameter names (e.g., "name: Alice" vs "Alice").

name: useNewlines
desc: Whether to use newlines between parameters.

name: TooFewPositionalArgumentException
desc:
Thrown when a runtime invocation receives fewer positional arguments
than the target function or constructor requires.

name: TooFewPositionalArgumentException.new
desc:
Thrown when a runtime invocation receives fewer positional arguments
than the target function or constructor requires.

name: actual
desc: The number of positional arguments actually supplied by the caller.

name: expected
desc: The number of required positional arguments expected by the target.

name: TooManyPositionalArgumentException
desc:
Thrown when a runtime invocation receives more positional arguments
than the target function or constructor accepts.

name: TooManyPositionalArgumentException.new
desc:
Thrown when a runtime invocation receives more positional arguments
than the target function or constructor accepts.

name: actual
desc: The number of positional arguments actually supplied.

name: expected
desc: The maximum number of positional arguments allowed by the target.

name: TryOutsideIsolate
desc:
Signature for a callback used to determine whether a file should be
processed outside an isolate.

name: TypeKind
desc:
Enumerates the different kinds of Dart types recognized by JetLeaf‚Äôs
reflection and type resolution system.

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: UnexpectedArgumentException
desc:
Thrown when an invocation receives an argument that does not correspond
to any declared parameter, usually a named parameter that the target
method or constructor does not define.

name: UnexpectedArgumentException.new
desc:
Thrown when an invocation receives an argument that does not correspond
to any declared parameter, usually a named parameter that the target
method or constructor does not define.

name: argumentName
desc: The name of the unexpected or undeclared argument.

name: UnresolvedClass
desc: Represents a class whose type could not be fully resolved at runtime.

name: getName
desc: Returns the simple name of the unresolved class.

name: UnresolvedClassExtension
desc: üîπ Extension: UnresolvedClassExtension

name: getWarningMessage
desc:
Generates a human-readable warning message for all unresolved classes
in this iterable.

name: UnresolvedTypeInstantiationException
desc:
Exception thrown when JetLeaf is unable to instantiate a class or resolve a
constructor because the runtime type is unresolved.

name: UnresolvedTypeInstantiationException.new
desc:
Exception thrown when JetLeaf is unable to instantiate a class or resolve a
constructor because the runtime type is unresolved.

name: UnsupportedRuntimeOperationException
desc:
Exception thrown when an operation cannot be performed due to runtime
environment limitations.

name: UnsupportedRuntimeOperationException.new
desc:
Exception thrown when an operation cannot be performed due to runtime
environment limitations.

name: Void
desc:
Abstract base class representing a marker or placeholder type in the
JetLeaf type system.

name: KEYWORD
desc: Internal keyword representing the JetLeaf void marker type.

name: getQualifiedName
desc: Returns the fully-qualified JetLeaf type identifier for the Void marker class.

name: getUri
desc: Returns the canonical Uri pointing to the JetLeaf library that declares Void.

name: forgetPackage
desc:
Returns true if the provided text contains a reference to a package
that should be excluded.

name: getNonNecessaryPackages
desc:
Returns a list of package names that are considered non-essential for
runtime analysis and should generally be excluded from scanning.

name: hashCode
desc: Computes a deep hash code for an object.

name: resolvePublicDartType
desc: Resolves a public Dart platform type using a library URI and class name.

name: runScan
desc:
Executes a full application runtime scan, builds a runtime context,
and registers it globally.

name: runTestScan
desc:
Executes a mock runtime scan and registers the resulting runtime
context for testing and validation purposes.
